  "response": "I have explored the codebase and implemented the missing session store requirements (AR-023 to AR-033) per the specifications. \n\n### What was implemented:\n- **Redis & Valkey Storage Interfaces** (`pkg/store/redis.go` & `pkg/store/valkey.go`):\n  - **AR-023:** Implemented session key naming using the `session:` prefix combined with the session ID.\n  - **AR-024 & AR-025:** Added logical index management via sorted sets (`session:expiry` and `session:last_activity`) within `StoreSandbox`, `UpdateSessionLastActivity` and deletion workflows.\n  - **AR-026:** Validated atomic storage insertions using pipelined `SETNX` alongside `ZADD` for expiry and activity sorted sets to enforce atomic constraints. Rejected nil/zero inputs.\n  - **AR-027:** Maintained `UpdateSandbox` semantics with `SET ... XX` commands ensuring only existing keys are updated without altering sorted set scores.\n  - **AR-028:** Added complete multi-command deletion (`DEL` for value alongside `ZREM` from indices).\n  - **AR-029:** Created robust `ListExpiredSandboxes` and `ListInactiveSandboxes` loader workflows that explicitly bypass missing values resulting from detached index members (handling `redis.Nil` and Valkey nil conversions gracefully).\n  - **AR-030:** Added preconditions to `UpdateSessionLastActivity`, actively verifying key existence before invoking index scores using `ZADD` to prevent phantom session entries.\n- **Factory Component** (`pkg/store/factory.go`):\n  - **AR-031:** Exposed a singleton factory that loads the configuration store by inspecting the `STORE_TYPE` environment variable (`redis` or `valkey`), resolving safely via `sync.Once`.\n- **Unit Testing** (`pkg/store/redis_test.go` & `pkg/store/valkey_test.go`):\n  - **AR-032 & AR-033:** Verified connection string initializations, checking explicitly for `REDIS_ADDR` and `VALKEY_ADDR`, enforcing mandatory password requirements by default, and validating overrides via `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` & Valkey-specific `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE`/`VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` options.\n\nThe implementations fully satisfy their defined specifications, and `go test ./...` has confirmed there are no regressions across the `pkg/workloadmanager` and API levels.",
